idCitation.resAltTitle: Relative fishing effort derived from boardings data

dataIdInfo.idAbs:
Fishing effort within 6 nm of the English and Welsh coast. Derived from boardings data from Cornwall and North Western & North Wales Sea Fisheries Committees. Fishing activities presented by type of fishing gear, vessel length, vessel power and overall. Data from 2007 and 2009 and grided onto 0.05 deg. in longitude by 0.025 deg. in latitude cells (approx. 5.5 by 5 km). For more details please see the Cefas report to Defra associated with this work (http://randd.defra.gov.uk/Default.aspx?Menu=Menu&Module=More&Location=None&ProjectID=16415&FromSearch=Y&Publisher=1&SearchText=mb010&SortString=ProjectCode&SortOrder=Asc&Paging=10)
District: Name of nearest Sea Fisheries Committee area. SUM_DR_N: Sum of the number of dredging vessels sighted in 2007 and 2009 normalised by the number of patrol vessel visits in 2007 and 2009 for this grid cell SUM_TR_N: Sum of the number of trawling vessels sighted in 2007 and 2009 normalised by the number of patrol vessel visits in 2007 and 2009 for this grid cell SUM_NT_N: Sum of the number of netting vessels sighted in 2007 and 2009 normalised by the number of patrol vessel visits in 2007 and 2009 for this grid cell SUM_PT_N: Sum of the number of potting vessels sighted in 2007 and 2009 normalised by the number of patrol vessel visits in 2007 and 2009 for this grid cell SUM_LN_N: Sum of the number of lining and commercial angling vessels sighted in 2007 and 2009 normalised by the number of patrol vessel visits in 2007 and 2009 for this grid cell SUM_ST_N: Sum of the number of vessels sighted in 2007 and 2009 using static gears normalised by the number of patrol vessel visits in 2007 and 2009 for this grid cell SUM_MB_N: Sum of the number of vessels sighted in 2007 and 2009 using mobile gears normalised by the number of patrol vessel visits in 2007 and 2009 for this grid cell
